
[title]
Functions: Callbacks

[execute index.html]
[time 3]

[explanation]

## Write a callback using the following two function

<pre class="code javascript" >
function download( callback ) { ... };
function save( file ) { ... };
</pre>

## Write a callback

*  _call_ `download` with the `callback` you create as the argument
* the `callback` you write should _accept_ an argument _(a file name)_
* use your `callback` to _call_ `save` with the file name, but only when it's **not null**

[zone name:script.js for:function_callbacks syntax:javascript]
download( /* callback */ )
[test source:test.js]
